protections.description: On June 15, 2020, the US Supreme Court ruled that employers subject to Title VII cannot hire, fire, or otherwise discriminate against employees based on their sexual orientation or gender identity.
Protection from being unfairly evicted, denied housing, or refused the ability to rent or buy housing.
Protection from being unfairly refused services or entry to or from places accessible to the public (retail stores, restaurants, parks, hotels, etc).
